{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Hybrid: Lightweight Account Layer\n      New Account entity (not a full org) that holds the Stripe subscription and owns buildings. Single-building buyers get an auto-created account. Management companies get a shared account. The account is mostly invisible in the UI for single-building users.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Supports both buyer types without over-engineering\n            Single-building users never see the account layer\n            Consolidated billing for management companies\n            Clean upgrade path to full org features if needed\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Still an extra entity, but thinner than a full org\n            Need to handle auto-creation logic during checkout\n            \"Invisible but present\" layer can be confusing if not documented well","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1774874946498}
